[[File:God of Saiha.png|thumb|right|170px|Saiha Shin]] '''Saiha Shin''' (歳破神, さいはしん) is one of the {{ill|Eight Guardian Deities|ja|八将神|1=Eight Directional Deities|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Guardian Deities|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Directional Deities|qq=}} in {{ill|Onmyōdō|ja|陰陽道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōdō|qq=}}. In certain calendars, it may also be written as "さいは" (Saiha). The {{ill|honji|ja|本地|1=Honji suijaku|2=ja|3=本地垂迹|lt=Honji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/honji|qq=}} of this deity is identified as {{ill|Hebo (Chinese deity)|ja|河伯|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hebo (Chinese deity)|qq=}}, the Great Water God.
Saiha Shin is regarded as the essence of {{ill|Saturn|ja|土星|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saturn|qq=}} (鎮星). This deity resides in the direction opposite that of {{ill|Taisai Shin (Tai Sui)|ja|太歳神|1=Taisai Shin|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taisai Shin (Tai Sui)|13=User:Immanuelle/Taisai Shin|qq=}}, another of the Eight Guardian Deities. However, it is said that Saiha Shin is often attacked and overpowered by Taisai Shin, which makes Saiha Shin a malevolent deity. Note that in {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星気学|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nine Star Ki|qq=}}, the directional term '''Saiha''' (歳破) is a distinct concept from the deity Saiha Shin.
Saiha Shin embodies the characteristics of {{ill|Earth (Wu Xing)|ja|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earth (Wu Xing)|qq=}}. It is considered inauspicious to perform actions like {{ill|earthworks|ja|動土|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/earthworks|qq=}} (e.g., land preparation or gardening), {{ill|construction|ja|建築|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/construction|qq=}}, {{ill|moving|ja|引越し|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/moving|qq=}}, {{ill|marriage|ja|婚姻|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/marriage|qq=}}, or {{ill|travel|ja|旅行|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/travel|qq=}}, particularly by ship, in the direction of Saiha Shin's presence. Violating this prohibition is said to bring harm to the head of a household or company. Additionally, seeking {{ill|pets|ja|ペット|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/pets|qq=}} or {{ill|livestock|ja|家畜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/livestock|qq=}} in the direction of this deity is considered unfavorable.
== Saiha Shin's Position == Saiha Shin resides in the direction opposite that of Taisai Shin, which aligns with the year’s {{ill|Chinese zodiac|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese zodiac|qq=}}: * Rat (子) → Horse (午) * Ox (丑) → Goat (未) * Tiger (寅) → Monkey (申) * Rabbit (卯) → Rooster (酉) * Dragon (辰) → Dog (戌) * Snake (巳) → Pig (亥) * Horse (午) → Rat (子) * Goat (未) → Ox (丑) * Monkey (申) → Tiger (寅) * Rooster (酉) → Rabbit (卯) * Dog (戌) → Dragon (辰) * Pig (亥) → Snake (巳) == See Also == * {{ill|Eight Guardian Deities|ja|八将神|1=Eight Directional Deities|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Guardian Deities|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Directional Deities|qq=}} * {{ill|Guardian Deity of Directions|ja|方位神|1=Directional deity|1=Directional deity|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Guardian Deity of Directions|13=User:Immanuelle/Directional deity|qq=}} * {{ill|Saiha|ja|歳破|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saiha|qq=}}・{{ill|Geppei|ja|月破|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Geppei|qq=}}
